AFP on the 12th, Port-au-PrinceA UN peacekeeping official told AFP that a UN police officer from Nigeria was shot to death by unidentified attackers today in Haiti."He was a riot policeman from Nigeria," said Combe, spokesperson for the UN Stabilization Mission in Haiti.The man, dressed in civilian clothes, was shot dead near a church in Port-au-Prince.The Haitian police found his dead body and turned it over to the UN officials.The shooting incident took place at a time when soaring food and fuel prices led to riots in Haiti, escalating political tensions.